{{Coord|32|33|28.13|N|47|19|29.72|E|display=title}} {{Infobox ancient site | name = Ali Kosh | image = Ganj dareh.jpg | caption = Map showing location of Ali Kosh and other locations of early herding activity | map = Neolithic sites in Iran.jpg | map_caption = Neolithic sites in Iran | location = [[Ilam Province]] | region = [[Iran]] | diameter = 135 m | cultures = [[Pre-Pottery Neolithic]] | discovered = 1960s | archaeologists = {{plainlist| * [[Frank Hole]] * [[Kent Flannery]] }} }}
'''Ali Kosh''' is a small [[Tell (archaeology)|Tell]] of the Early [[Neolithic]] period located in [[Ilam Province]] in west [[Iran]], in the [[Zagros Mountains]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://campuspress.yale.edu/frankhole/ali_kosh/ |title=Ali Kosh |first=Frank |last=Hole |author-link=Frank Hole |access-date=25 September 2018 |work=Yale Campus Press |publisher=[[Yale University]]}}</ref> It was excavated by [[Frank Hole]] and [[Kent Flannery]] in the 1960s.<ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095402701 |title=The Concise Oxford Dictionary of Archaeology |edition=2nd |first=Timothy |last=Darvill |author-link=Timothy Darvill |isbn=9780191727139 |year=2008 |doi=10.1093/acref/9780199534043.001.0001 |publisher=[[Oxford Reference]]}}</ref>
The site is about 135 m in diameter.<ref name=Smith>{{cite book |last=Smith |first=Andrew Brown |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OrLWtk0QXRYC&pg=PA68 |title=African herders: emergence of pastoral traditions |pages=67-68 |year=2005 |isbn=978-0-cite7591-0748-9 |publisher=[[Rowman Altamira]]}}</ref>
Research has found three phases of occupation of the site over an almost 2,000 period, starting from about 9,500 years ago (7500 BCE).<ref name=Smith/> It was occupied by pre-pottery peoples.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[An Encyclopedia of World History]] |last=Langer |first=William L. |author-link=William L. Langer |edition=5th |publisher=[[Houghton Mifflin Company]] |location=Boston, MA |year=1972 |isbn=0-395-13592-3 |page=17 |lccn=72186219}}</ref>
